    "title": "Why Learning Programming Matters for Beginners",
    "body_content": [
      {
        "text": "Programming is the process of creating, evaluating, and executing code to create useful, useful, and useful software.",
        "highlight_type": "definition",
        "term": "Programming"
      },
      {
        "text": "Learning to program lets you create, analyze, and share ideas, enabling creative work that improves your own mental state and improves the quality of your work.",
        "highlight_type": "key_concept",
        "term": null
      },
      {
        "text": "Computers act as personal assistants that manage hardware, operating systems, and applications, allowing you to manage data, work, and have fun.",
        "highlight_type": "example",
        "term": null
      }
    ],
